'''Swamp Crabs''' are [[aggressive]] monsters that disguise themselves as harmless Swampy logs. When a player approaches them, they will attack in a fashion that is identical to [[Rock Crab]]s. They can be found in multi-combat areas directly south of [[Port Phasmatys]] and along the path leading from Port Phasmatys to [[Slepe]]. It is recommended that lower-level players wanting to kill these stay near Port Phasmatys, as the path traverses through the [[Haunted Woods]] and players may encounter [[Feral Vampyre|Feral Vampyres]] and [[Leech|Leeches]].

Swamp Crabs will become unaggressive after a while, and can then only be examined as a Swampy log, giving the message "A bit of decaying wood". They will become aggressive again after leaving and re-entering their aggression radius.

If a player casts [[bloom]] while fighting a Swamp Crab, then its "shell" will grow three [[mort myre fungi|Mort Myre Fungi]], which will be dropped once it is killed. A good tactic to obtain additional fungi is to lure a Swamp Crab next to a [[Rotting log]], which will also have a chance of spawning some fungi after casting bloom.

Unlike other crabs, Swamp Crabs boast higher melee and magic defence, so it is generally not recommended to use these attack styles. Rather, due to their significantly reduced ranged defence, they are ideal for low-level to mid-level Ranged training.
